{{Infobox person | name = Bruna Esih | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|5|20}} | birth_place = [[Split, Croatia|Split]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]] | occupation = politica, philosopher, historian and croatologist | networth = | spouse = Renato Esih | children = 3 | residence = [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]] | alma_mater = Croatian Studies, Zagreb | website = | signature = | parents = }} '''Bruna Esih''' (born 20 May 1975) is a Croatian politician, philosopher, historian and croatologist, currently serving as president of political party [[Independents for Croatia]]. She is one of the most popular conservative politicians in [[Croatia]].<ref> Karlović-Sabolić, Marina. [https://www.slobodnadalmacija.hr/novosti/hrvatska/clanak/id/470275/bruna-esih-zvijezda-hrvatske-politike-i-ikona-desnice-hoce-li-roena-splicanka-osvojiti-zagreb-i-tako-zapoceti-karijeru-iz-snova Bruna Esih, zvijezda hrvatske politike i ikona desnice: hoće li rođena Splićanka osvojiti Zagreb i tako započeti karijeru iz snova?] Slobodna Dalmacija. Published 23-02-2017. Access date 28-04-2018. </ref> She has called for [[lustration]] and [[decommunisation]] in Croatia.<ref> [https://kamenjar.com/bruna-esih-lustracija-pojam-tijekom-27-godina-poprimio-lose-konotacije/ Bruna Esih: Lustracija je pojam koji je tijekom 27 godina poprimio loše konotacije] Kamenjar.com. Published 26-10-2016. Access date 28-04-2018.</ref>
== Works == She researched [[Bleiburg massacre]] and [[Battle of Vukovar]] as well as partisan crimes after [[World War Two]] in [[Second Yugoslavia]]. She is co-author of three books as a scientist on Ivo Pilar Institute in Zagreb. She was special delegate of Croatian president [[Kolinda Grabar-Kitarović]] for Bleiburg commemorations.<ref> [https://direktno.hr/direkt/izaslanica-esih-kolinda-na-bleiburgu-nije-bila-sama-nego-s-dusama-mrtvih-15090/ Izaslanica Esih: Kolinda na Bleiburgu nije bila sama, nego s dušama mrtvih] Direktno.hr. Published 15-05-2015. Access date 28-04-2018. </ref>
* ''Čuvari bleiburške uspomene'', Zagreb, 2003. * ''Vukovar '91: međunarodni odjeci i značaj'', zagreb, 2004. * ''Bleiburg Memento'', Zagreb, 2005.
She co-operated alongside historian [[Josip Jurčević]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}}
