'''Ramón Meza y Suárez Inclán''' (born January 28, 1861—1911), was a Cuban literary critic, historian, professor and Doctor in Philosophy and Literature at the [[University of Havana]], and also author of many works of both fiction and non-fiction.<ref name=meza>{{cite web|url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n85130581.html|title=Meza y Suárez Inclán, Ramón, 1861-1911-Authorities & Vocabularies|publisher=Library of Congress|accessdate=January 5, 2012}}</ref><ref name=vega>García Vega, Lorenzo. ''Antología de la novela cubana''. (1960). Dirección General de Cultura, Ministerio de Educación.</ref><ref name=baquero>Baquero, Gastón; Báez, Vicente. ''La enciclopedia de Cuba:Volume 3''. (1975). Enciclopedia y Clásicos Cubanos. {{ISBN|9788435901765}} {{ISBN|8435901769}}</ref><ref name=obaya>Obaya, Alicia; Barredo, Gloria; Ricardo, Yolanda. (2002) ''Valoraciones sobre temas y problemas de la literatura cubana: part 2.'' Editorial Pueblo y Educación. {{ISBN|9789591309525}}</ref><ref name=biblioteca>Biblioteca Nacional (Cuba). (1910). ''Revista  de la Biblioteca Nacional, volumen 2-3.''</ref>

==Life==

When he was 17 years of age, he enrolled in the [[University of Havana]], where he majored in 1882 in Civil Law.

Two years later, his first literary reviews were published. He contributed extensively to the periodicals ''La lotería'', to ''Revista de Cuba'', and ''Cuba en América''.<ref name=baquero/>

In July 7, 1900, he was appointed Subsecretary of Justice, filling in the position for Alfredo Zayas y Alfonso.<ref name=biblioteca/><ref name=civil>Wood, Leonard. ''Civil report, 1899-1900, volume 2.'' (1900). s. n. [https://books.google.com/books?id=Z9cCAAAAYAAJ p. 626]</ref><ref>Wood, Leonard.''Report of the military governor of Cuba on civil affairs, volume 1, part 1.'' (1901). Government printing office.[https://books.google.com/books?id=N2gWAAAAYAAJ p. 497]</ref>

A month later, in August 17, 1900, he resigned the position to which he had been appointed, and was replaced by Gastón Mora y Varona.<ref>United States War Dept. ''Annual reports, volume 1.'' (1901). Government printing office. [https://books.google.com/books?id=MTgqIgMaHuACp. 535]</ref>

In 1900, he wrote an article for the faculty at the [[University of Havana]] titled ''Don Quijote como tipo ideal'' ({{lang-en|Don Quixote as the ideal kind}}), in which he paid tribute to Cervante's masterpiece ''Don Quijote de la Mancha''.<ref name=facultad>Universidad de la Habana; Facultad de letras y ciencias. ''Revista de la Facultad de letras y ciencias, volume 1.'' (1901). Universidad de la Habana.[https://books.google.com/books?id=66MKAAAAYAAJ p.]</ref>

